{"author":"Joe Oakhart","author_email":"joeoakhart+bot@navapbc.com","author_id":"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d","author_sig":"{\"payload\": \"\", \"payloadType\": \"application/vnd.rebar.authorship.v1+json\", \"signatures\": [{\"keyid\": \"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d\", \"sig\": \"\"}]}","data":{"coaching":[{"coaching":"Pin down the event-uuid absence verification command with a concrete worked example.","decision":"block","finding_refs":["f3b0873b9f1f93b17","f9085068f07d49b63","f56a6d5c764487a77"],"move_id":"6","move_name":"specification by example","subject":"the event-uuid absence verification command"},{"coaching":"Plan how the LINK-event-specific signed field check will be verified in-session — restate any deferred or unobservable success target as an observable proxy.","decision":"block","finding_refs":["fd2129d957af1e94c","f37717daa9f05a4ea"],"move_id":"9","move_name":"plan the verification","subject":"the LINK-event-specific signed field check"},{"coaching":"State the concrete attestation evidence the [operator-attested] the container-inspection fallback as canary substitute will require (a change id / vote outcome / timestamp), recorded on the ticket.","decision":"advisory","finding_refs":["fbb70edf5b834bcc2"],"move_id":"14","move_name":"state attestation evidence","subject":"the container-inspection fallback as canary substitute"},{"coaching":"Plan how the acceptance-criteria proving commands will be verified in-session — restate any deferred or unobservable success target as an observable proxy.","decision":"advisory","finding_refs":["f607dd457c67f9209"],"move_id":"9","move_name":"plan the verification","subject":"the acceptance-criteria proving commands"}],"coverage":{"counts":{"advisory_overflow":0,"advisory_surfaced":5,"blocking":2,"dropped":2,"indeterminate":0},"det":{"P1":{"ac_items":4,"blocking":false,"clarity_score":7,"name":"readiness-shape","ran":true,"status":"pass"},"P2":{"blocking":false,"name":"resolution","ran":true,"references":0,"resolved":0,"status":"pass"},"P3":{"blocking":false,"name":"package-existence","packages":0,"ran":true,"status":"pass"},"P4":{"ac_items":4,"blocking":false,"desc_chars":5706,"file_impact":4,"name":"oversize","ran":true,"status":"pass"},"P5":{"blocking":false,"children":0,"name":"task-dag","ran":true,"status":"pass"},"P6":{"ac_items":4,"blocking":false,"name":"ac-quality","ran":true,"status":"fail","verify_commands_linted":57,"verify_lint_abstained":56},"P7":{"blocking":false,"destructive_hits":[],"name":"destructive-sniff","ran":true,"status":"pass"},"P8":{"blocking":false,"budget_tokens":868000,"name":"reviewability","plan_tokens":1448,"ran":true,"status":"pass"},"P9":{"applicable":true,"blocking":false,"file_impact":4,"name":"file-impact-coverage","ran":true,"status":"pass"}},"llm_ran":true,"metrics":{"claim_path":"no-llm/no-network (structural; the fast claim check is a local HMAC verify)","det_ms":257.7,"llm_calls":30,"llm_ms":426141.3,"total_ms":426502.6,"verify_requests":34},"remediation":{"baseline":"sidecar","eligible":true,"reasons":{"code_unchanged":true,"plan_changed":true,"registry_unchanged":true,"sidecar_baseline":true,"within_window":true}},"routing":{"agent_tier":["A1","E4","G1G2","G6","G7","T1","T10","T11","T13","T14","T3","T5c","T8","removal-rationale"],"single_turn":["COH","E1","E2","E3","E5","E6","F1","G5","T12","T2","T4","T5b","T5d","T5e","T6","T7","T9","hedge"]}},"findings":[{"block_threshold":0.7,"blocking_enabled":true,"checklist_item":"","cohort":null,"criteria":["T8"],"decision":"block","drop_reason":null,"evidence":[],"finding":"The AC2 (and AC4) proving command `jq --arg u E -e 'all(.[]; .event_uuid != $u)'` contains a structural defect: `--arg u E` passes the *literal string* \"E\" as jq's `$u` variable (jq's `--arg name value` syntax), not the shell variable expansion of `E`. An operator copying this verbatim will always get exit 0 — the filter trivially passes because no real event uuid equals the literal character 'E' — producing a false-green verification regardless of whether the LINK event actually appears in the non-verified report.","group_criteria":null,"group_id":null,"id":"f3b0873b9f1f93b17","impact":1.0,"is_primary":null,"location":"AC2 proving command: `rebar verify-identity --all --format json | jq --arg u E -e 'all(.[]; .event_uuid != $u)'`; also repeated in AC4 operator-attested block","norm_id":"n6fcc7a16314d1301","priority":0.875,"reason":"high-priority+criterion-opted-in","scenarios":[],"severity":"critical","suggested_fix":"Replace the bare `E` in the jq call with a quoted shell expansion. Full corrected sequence for AC2:\n```sh\nE=<uuid recorded from the LINK event above>\nrebar verify-identity --all --format json \\\n  | jq --arg u \"$E\" -e 'all(.[]; .event_uuid != $u)'\n```\nThe double-quoted `\"$E\"` causes the shell to expand the variable before passing its value to jq as the `--arg` literal.","tier":"LLM","validity":0.875,"verification":{"binary":{"absence_confirmed_in_context":"na","cited_reference_accurate":"na","claims_absence":"no","committed_work_relies_on_unbacked_claim":"na","evidence_entails_finding":"yes","impact_follows_necessarily":"yes","is_verifiable":"yes","no_existing_mitigation":"no","no_viable_alternative_explanation":"yes","path_reachable":"yes","respects_artifact_altitude":"yes","severity_claim_justified":"yes"},"severity_attributes":{"ac_unverifiable":"broken_oracle","blast_radius":"local","debt_impact":"none","divergent_implementation":"none","dod_uncertifiable":"high","internal_conflict":"none","irreversible_without_rationale":"none","likelihood":"high","prod_impact":"none","reversibility":"easy","silent_vs_self_revealing":"silent","undecomposed":"none","vague_directive":"none"}}},{"block_threshold":0.6,"blocking_enabled":true,"checklist_item":"","cohort":null,"criteria":["E6","F1"],"decision":"block","drop_reason":null,"evidence":[],"finding":"The first half of AC2's proving command (`rebar show <t> | jq -e '.authorship.signed >= 1'`) checks an aggregate field on the work ticket, not the specific LINK event written by the review-bot. If the work ticket already has one or more signed events from other authors, this check passes even if the bot's reciprocal LINK event is unsigned, giving a false-green result for the criterion 'signature present on the LINK-target ticket'.","group_criteria":null,"group_id":null,"id":"fd2129d957af1e94c","impact":1.0,"is_primary":null,"location":"AC2: `rebar show <t> | jq -e '.authorship.signed >= 1'`","norm_id":"n42561480543d135e","priority":0.6875,"reason":"high-priority+criterion-opted-in","scenarios":[],"severity":"critical","suggested_fix":"Replace:\n```\nrebar show <t> | jq -e '.authorship.signed >= 1'\n```\nWith (after `export E=<uuid>`):\n```\nrebar show <t> | jq --arg u \"$E\" -e '.events[] | select(.uuid == $u) | .signed == true'\n```\nThis isolates the signature assertion to the bot's specific LINK event.","tier":"LLM","validity":0.6875,"verification":{"binary":{"absence_confirmed_in_context":"na","cited_reference_accurate":"na","claims_absence":"no","committed_work_relies_on_unbacked_claim":"na","evidence_entails_finding":"yes","impact_follows_necessarily":"no","is_verifiable":"yes","no_existing_mitigation":"no","no_viable_alternative_explanation":"yes","path_reachable":"yes","respects_artifact_altitude":"yes","severity_claim_justified":"insufficient"},"severity_attributes":{"ac_unverifiable":"broken_oracle","blast_radius":"local","debt_impact":"none","divergent_implementation":"none","dod_uncertifiable":"none","internal_conflict":"none","irreversible_without_rationale":"none","likelihood":"medium","prod_impact":"none","reversibility":"easy","silent_vs_self_revealing":"silent","undecomposed":"none","vague_directive":"none"}}},{"block_threshold":0.95,"blocking_enabled":false,"checklist_item":"- [ ] Fix the jq proving commands in AC2 and AC4 to shell-expand the uuid variable before passing to jq: replace `jq --arg u E` with `jq --arg u \"$E\"` (where `E` is the shell variable name holding the recorded event uuid), or equivalently use `jq --argjson`/`--arg` with proper quoting.","cohort":["T3"],"criteria":["T3"],"decision":"advisory","drop_reason":null,"evidence":["Plan AC2: `rebar verify-identity --all --format json | jq --arg u E -e 'all(.[]; .event_uuid != $u)'`","Plan AC4: same pattern — `rebar verify-identity --all --format json | jq --arg u E -e 'all(.[]; .event_uuid != $u)'`","jq CLI: `--arg name value` passes the literal string `value` — shell variable expansion must happen before jq invocation, requiring `--arg u \"$E\"` with double-quoted shell variable","Cached review evidence confirms this exact defect was flagged on related tickets: `.rebar/cache/plan-review/1a51-b170-5168-46d2/41d3f78cce10e73cff32.json`, `6709f3fd88e8050bb0b1.json`","Evidence class: Verified (jq --arg semantics are stable and well-documented; the literal-vs-variable distinction is a factual CLI flag mismatch)"],"finding":"The AC2 (and AC4) proving command `jq --arg u E -e 'all(.[]; .event_uuid != $u)'` is mechanically broken at the CLI flag level: jq's `--arg name value` syntax assigns the *literal token* `value` to jq variable `$name`, so `--arg u E` sets `$u = \"E\"` (the four-character string), not the shell variable `$E` holding the recorded event uuid. As written, the command compares every event_uuid to the literal string 'E', exits 0 trivially, and provides no actual verification — the signed LINK event could appear in the non-verified report undetected.","group_criteria":null,"group_id":null,"id":"f9085068f07d49b63","impact":1.0,"is_primary":null,"location":"AC2 proving command; AC4 (operator-attested) proving command","norm_id":"n3491250729a44615","priority":0.875,"reason":"default-advisory","scenarios":["Operator runs the proving command with the literal placeholder 'E' unsubstituted; jq exits 0 regardless of store contents, giving a false pass.","Operator substitutes a real uuid but uses the command exactly as written; `--arg u <uuid>` works correctly in that case — but the plan writes `E` not `<uuid>`, inviting copy-paste errors."],"severity":"critical","suggested_fix":"Replace `jq --arg u E -e 'all(.[]; .event_uuid != $u)'` with `jq --arg u \"$E\" -e 'all(.[]; .event_uuid != $u)'` in both AC2 and AC4, and make explicit that `E` is a shell variable (e.g., `E=<recorded-uuid>`) set before running the command.","tier":"LLM","validity":0.875,"verification":{"binary":{"absence_confirmed_in_context":"na","cited_reference_accurate":"yes","claims_absence":"no","committed_work_relies_on_unbacked_claim":"na","evidence_entails_finding":"yes","impact_follows_necessarily":"yes","is_verifiable":"yes","no_existing_mitigation":"no","no_viable_alternative_explanation":"yes","path_reachable":"yes","respects_artifact_altitude":"yes","severity_claim_justified":"yes"},"severity_attributes":{"ac_unverifiable":"broken_oracle","blast_radius":"local","debt_impact":"none","divergent_implementation":"none","dod_uncertifiable":"high","internal_conflict":"none","irreversible_without_rationale":"none","likelihood":"high","prod_impact":"none","reversibility":"easy","silent_vs_self_revealing":"silent","undecomposed":"none","vague_directive":"none"}}},{"block_threshold":0.95,"blocking_enabled":false,"checklist_item":"","cohort":null,"criteria":["E6"],"decision":"advisory","drop_reason":null,"evidence":[],"finding":"The proving command `jq --arg u E -e 'all(.[]; .event_uuid != $u)'` passes the literal four-character string \"E\" to jq — not the shell variable holding the actual event uuid — because `--arg u E` is a positional argument, not a shell expansion. An operator copying the command verbatim will silently test for the absence of the literal string \"E\" from the report, which always passes, producing a false-green result.","group_criteria":null,"group_id":null,"id":"f56a6d5c764487a77","impact":1.0,"is_primary":null,"location":"AC2 proving command: `rebar verify-identity --all --format json | jq --arg u E -e 'all(.[]; .event_uuid != $u)'`","norm_id":"n9ac527a94a3c08f8","priority":0.875,"reason":"default-advisory","scenarios":[],"severity":"critical","suggested_fix":"Add before the command: `export E=<uuid recorded above>`, then:\n```\nrebar verify-identity --all --format json \\\n  | jq --arg u \"$E\" -e 'all(.[]; .event_uuid != $u)'\n```\nThe double-quoted `\"$E\"` ensures the shell expands the variable before passing it to jq.","tier":"LLM","validity":0.875,"verification":{"binary":{"absence_confirmed_in_context":"na","cited_reference_accurate":"na","claims_absence":"no","committed_work_relies_on_unbacked_claim":"na","evidence_entails_finding":"yes","impact_follows_necessarily":"yes","is_verifiable":"yes","no_existing_mitigation":"no","no_viable_alternative_explanation":"yes","path_reachable":"yes","respects_artifact_altitude":"yes","severity_claim_justified":"yes"},"severity_attributes":{"ac_unverifiable":"broken_oracle","blast_radius":"local","debt_impact":"none","divergent_implementation":"none","dod_uncertifiable":"high","internal_conflict":"none","irreversible_without_rationale":"none","likelihood":"high","prod_impact":"none","reversibility":"easy","silent_vs_self_revealing":"silent","undecomposed":"none","vague_directive":"none"}}},{"block_threshold":0.95,"blocking_enabled":false,"checklist_item":"- [ ] Tighten AC2's first proving command to assert on the LINK event specifically rather than the ticket aggregate — e.g., inspect the event list for the uuid E directly: `rebar show <t> --events | jq -e --arg u \"$E\" 'any(.[]; .uuid == $u and .authorship.signed == true)'`, or drop the aggregate check and let the uuid-specific second command be the sole gate, with a note that it is the definitive proof.","cohort":["E2","E6","F1"],"criteria":["E6"],"decision":"advisory","drop_reason":null,"evidence":["\"Proving evidence: rebar show <t> | jq -e '.authorship.signed >= 1' (signature present on the LINK-target ticket)\"","The aggregate `.authorship.signed` counts ALL signed events on the ticket, not only the LINK event; a pre-existing signed event satisfies `>= 1` independently of whether the new LINK event carries a signature.","Verify-command defect taxonomy: fixture invalidity — the command does not exercise the specific claim (LINK event is signed)."],"finding":"AC2's first proving command (`rebar show <t> | jq -e '.authorship.signed >= 1'`) checks a ticket-level aggregate signed count, not the specific LINK event. If the work ticket already has any other signed event (e.g., a signed creation event predating this story), the command exits 0 even if the new LINK event is unsigned — a fixture-invalidity false positive that AC2's second command (uuid-specific absence from the non-verified report) is meant to catch but that makes the first command misleading as standalone evidence of 'the LINK event is signed'.","group_criteria":null,"group_id":null,"id":"f37717daa9f05a4ea","impact":1.0,"is_primary":null,"location":"Acceptance Criteria — AC2, proving command 1: `rebar show <t> | jq -e '.authorship.signed >= 1'`","norm_id":"n7bf86331ae5547ff","priority":0.625,"reason":"default-advisory","scenarios":["Work ticket <t> was created with a signed CREATE event before this story; `authorship.signed >= 1` passes at the moment the review-bot LINK is written even if the bot never signed it, masking a signing malfunction."],"severity":"critical","suggested_fix":"Replace the aggregate check with an event-specific assertion, e.g.:\n```\nrebar show <t> --events | jq -e --arg u \"$E\" 'any(.[]; .uuid == $u and (.signature // \"\") != \"\")'\n```\nor simply remove the first command and document that the second command (`all(.[]; .event_uuid != $u)` against the non-verified report) is the sole definitive gate, since it is already event-uuid-specific.","tier":"LLM","validity":0.625,"verification":{"binary":{"absence_confirmed_in_context":"na","cited_reference_accurate":"yes","claims_absence":"no","committed_work_relies_on_unbacked_claim":"na","evidence_entails_finding":"yes","impact_follows_necessarily":"no","is_verifiable":"yes","no_existing_mitigation":"no","no_viable_alternative_explanation":"yes","path_reachable":"yes","respects_artifact_altitude":"yes","severity_claim_justified":"no"},"severity_attributes":{"ac_unverifiable":"broken_oracle","blast_radius":"local","debt_impact":"low","divergent_implementation":"none","dod_uncertifiable":"none","internal_conflict":"none","irreversible_without_rationale":"none","likelihood":"medium","prod_impact":"none","reversibility":"easy","silent_vs_self_revealing":"silent","undecomposed":"none","vague_directive":"none"}}},{"block_threshold":0.95,"blocking_enabled":false,"checklist_item":"- [ ] Remove or demote the 'Fallback: inspect the running review-bot container on the VM via AWS SSM...' sentence from the 'Confirming canary 1787' section so it cannot be read as a substitute completion path; if SSM inspection is retained for diagnostic mention, add the same qualification as AC4 ('supplementary diagnostic context only, never a substitute for the signed event').","cohort":["E3","T6","T9"],"criteria":["E3"],"decision":"advisory","drop_reason":null,"evidence":["Body: 'Fallback: inspect the running review-bot container on the VM via AWS SSM to confirm the key is materialized and REBAR_IDENTITY_SIGNING_KEY is set.'","AC4: 'A materialized key is not sufficient — it does not prove the bot signs, and could mask a signing malfunction. Required evidence recorded on this ticket: the signed LINK event uuid E...'","AC4: 'A container/SSM inspection...may be recorded as supplementary diagnostic context only, never as a substitute for the signed event.'"],"finding":"The 'Confirming canary 1787' section introduces a 'Fallback: inspect the running review-bot container on the VM via AWS SSM to confirm the key is materialized and REBAR_IDENTITY_SIGNING_KEY is set' — implying SSM key inspection is an acceptable substitute if the happy path is unavailable — but AC4 explicitly states 'A materialized key is not sufficient — it does not prove the bot signs, and could mask a signing malfunction' and prohibits it as a substitute. This internal contradiction could cause an operator to use the SSM inspection as the primary proof rather than the required signed-event evidence.","group_criteria":null,"group_id":null,"id":"fbb70edf5b834bcc2","impact":0.67,"is_primary":null,"location":"'Confirming canary 1787' section (fallback sentence) vs AC4 ([operator-attested] checklist item)","norm_id":"nc2a3fbf280ad7c6a","priority":0.4188,"reason":"default-advisory","scenarios":["Operator pushes a Gerrit change but no review-bot LINK appears (e.g., bot misconfigured, signing code path broken); operator falls back to SSM key inspection, finds the key is materialized, and marks canary 1787 complete — missing an actual signing malfunction."],"severity":"major","suggested_fix":"Replace the 'Fallback' sentence in 'Confirming canary 1787' with: '(Diagnostic only, not a completion substitute: if the LINK event does not appear, you may inspect the container via AWS SSM — `aws ssm start-session … docker exec … env | grep REBAR_IDENTITY_SIGNING_KEY` — to triage key materialization, but this does not satisfy the canary; a signed, verified LINK event uuid is required per AC4.)'","tier":"LLM","validity":0.625,"verification":{"binary":{"absence_confirmed_in_context":"na","cited_reference_accurate":"yes","claims_absence":"no","committed_work_relies_on_unbacked_claim":"na","evidence_entails_finding":"yes","impact_follows_necessarily":"no","is_verifiable":"yes","no_existing_mitigation":"no","no_viable_alternative_explanation":"no","path_reachable":"yes","respects_artifact_altitude":"yes","severity_claim_justified":"yes"},"severity_attributes":{"ac_unverifiable":"none","blast_radius":"local","debt_impact":"none","divergent_implementation":"none","dod_uncertifiable":"none","internal_conflict":"medium","irreversible_without_rationale":"none","likelihood":"medium","prod_impact":"low","reversibility":"easy","silent_vs_self_revealing":"silent","undecomposed":"none","vague_directive":"none"}}},{"block_threshold":null,"blocking_enabled":null,"checklist_item":"","cohort":null,"criteria":["P6"],"decision":"advisory","drop_reason":null,"evidence":["vague/subjective terms present: sufficient","verify command `aws ssm start-session … docker exec … env | grep REBAR_IDENTITY_SIGNING_KEY` greps the unanchored word 'REBAR_IDENTITY_SIGNING_KEY' — it substring-matches (e.g. 'review_REBAR_IDENTITY_SIGNING_KEY'); anchor it (\\b, ^$, or a quoted key like '\"REBAR_IDENTITY_SIGNING_KEY\":')"],"finding":"Acceptance-criteria / definition-of-done quality issues.","group_criteria":null,"group_id":null,"id":"f607dd457c67f9209","impact":0.4,"is_primary":null,"location":"","norm_id":"ned06ebc801a522e3","priority":0.4,"reason":null,"scenarios":[],"severity":"minor","suggested_fix":"Split compound criteria, replace subjective terms with observable outcomes, and state how each is verified.","tier":"DET","validity":1.0,"verification":null},{"block_threshold":0.7,"blocking_enabled":true,"checklist_item":"- [ ] Add the `REVIEW_RESULT` sidecar write (`voter.py:253` → `code_review/sidecar.py:143`, writes to the `code_review` artifact ticket) as an explicit line in the classification table, classified GATE-EXEMPT (same reason: `code_review ∈ _GATE_EXEMPT_TYPES`).","cohort":["G1G2"],"criteria":["G1G2"],"decision":"dropped","drop_reason":null,"evidence":["voter.py:253-260: sidecar.emit(verdict, target_ticket=artifact_id, ...) is a separate append_event call beyond the create_ticket at :241-251","code_review/sidecar.py:143: append_event(target_ticket, EVENT_TYPE, payload, tracker, repo_root=repo_root) — EVENT_TYPE='REVIEW_RESULT'","The AC1 criterion states 'Every Gerrit-side store operation is enumerated and classified'; the REVIEW_RESULT sidecar emit is a distinct store write (event type + ticket target) not listed separately"],"finding":"The classification table claims to enumerate 'every Gerrit-side store operation' but does not explicitly list the REVIEW_RESULT sidecar write (voter.py:253 → code_review/sidecar.py:143, which calls _seam.append_event on the code_review artifact ticket) as a distinct store operation. It is implicitly subsumed under the 'code_review artifact → GATE-EXEMPT' bullet, but a reader auditing the table would not see it called out separately.","group_criteria":null,"group_id":null,"id":"fc41f957f8f81072a","impact":0.33,"is_primary":null,"location":"What — enumerate and classify every Gerrit-side store operation / 'review-bot code_review artifact → GATE-EXEMPT' bullet","norm_id":"ne147f3e3ee7fcbe1","priority":0.0943,"reason":"veto:absence-refuted","scenarios":["An auditor reviewing the classification table to confirm completeness for the AC1 criterion would not find the REVIEW_RESULT sidecar event listed, creating a gap in the evidence record even though the classification outcome (gate-exempt via code_review ticket type) is correct."],"severity":"minor","suggested_fix":"Add a bullet: '**review-bot `REVIEW_RESULT` sidecar on the `code_review` artifact → GATE-EXEMPT.** `voter.py:253` calls `sidecar.emit(verdict, target_ticket=artifact_id, ...)` → `code_review/sidecar.py:143` (`append_event(target_ticket, \"REVIEW_RESULT\", ...)`) — writes to the same gate-exempt `code_review` ticket; exemption applies by ticket type.'","tier":"LLM","validity":0.2857,"verification":{"binary":{"absence_confirmed_in_context":"no","cited_reference_accurate":"yes","claims_absence":"yes","committed_work_relies_on_unbacked_claim":"na","evidence_entails_finding":"no","impact_follows_necessarily":"no","is_verifiable":"yes","no_existing_mitigation":"no","no_viable_alternative_explanation":"no","path_reachable":"na","respects_artifact_altitude":"yes","severity_claim_justified":"no"},"severity_attributes":{"ac_unverifiable":"none","blast_radius":"local","debt_impact":"none","divergent_implementation":"none","dod_uncertifiable":"none","internal_conflict":"none","irreversible_without_rationale":"none","likelihood":"low","prod_impact":"none","reversibility":"easy","silent_vs_self_revealing":"","undecomposed":"none","vague_directive":"low"}}},{"block_threshold":0.7,"blocking_enabled":true,"checklist_item":"- [ ] Verify and cite the mechanism by which the review-bot container resolves ambient git identity to `joeoakhart+bot@navapbc.com` (e.g. a `GIT_AUTHOR_EMAIL` env var, entrypoint `git config`, or `REBAR_IDENTITY_EMAIL` env var in docker-compose.yml), so that LINK events carry `author_id=594c` and the seam actually signs them.","cohort":["T1"],"criteria":["T1"],"decision":"dropped","drop_reason":null,"evidence":["Plan: 'the write seam (_seam.py:294-315) signs when a resolvable `author_id` (594c, via the bot git email) + a `signing_key` are present'","_seam.py:293-294: `author_id = event.get('author_id')` / `if author_id and signing_key:` — signing is silently skipped if author_id is absent","No cited docker-compose env var, entrypoint config, or git config that sets `user.email=joeoakhart+bot@navapbc.com` in the review-bot container context","ABSENCE: the plan does not reference any mechanism by which the review-bot container resolves the ambient identity to 594c when calling append_event for LINK events"],"finding":"The plan asserts that the review-bot's LINK events will carry `author_id=594c` (enabling the seam to sign them), but does not verify that the review-bot container has git user email configured to `joeoakhart+bot@navapbc.com`. The seam's `_apply_authorship` only signs when `author_id` is non-null on the event; `author_id` is resolved from the ambient git identity at write time. If the container's git email is absent or wrong, the LINK event is written unsigned without any error (the broad except at `_seam.py:306` catches signing failures, but the no-`author_id` path at line 293-294 is a silent skip, not an error). This is an unverified capability assertion — the plan does not cite the container's git config or entrypoint setup that would guarantee identity resolution.","group_criteria":null,"group_id":null,"id":"fabc7b100457b7e9c","impact":0.0,"is_primary":null,"location":"What section — 'Already provisioned to sign' paragraph; also _seam.py:293-294","norm_id":"n571d0722345d1028","priority":0.0,"reason":"veto:absence-refuted","scenarios":["If the review-bot container's git config lacks user.email (or has the wrong email), append_event populates author_id as 'Unknown' or empty, _apply_authorship skips signing silently, and the LINK event is written unsigned — the canary run would then produce an unsigned event rather than a signed one, and AC2/AC4 would fail at operator verification time rather than being caught by the plan spec."],"severity":"none","suggested_fix":"","tier":"LLM","validity":0.5556,"verification":{"binary":{"absence_confirmed_in_context":"no","cited_reference_accurate":"insufficient","claims_absence":"yes","committed_work_relies_on_unbacked_claim":"yes","evidence_entails_finding":"no","impact_follows_necessarily":"no","is_verifiable":"yes","no_existing_mitigation":"yes","no_viable_alternative_explanation":"no","path_reachable":"yes","respects_artifact_altitude":"yes","severity_claim_justified":"no"},"severity_attributes":{"ac_unverifiable":"none","blast_radius":"local","debt_impact":"none","divergent_implementation":"none","dod_uncertifiable":"none","internal_conflict":"none","irreversible_without_rationale":"none","likelihood":"low","prod_impact":"none","reversibility":"easy","silent_vs_self_revealing":"","undecomposed":"none","vague_directive":"none"}}}],"impact_model_version":"plan-v3","material_fingerprint":"13366697b49692cb","metrics":{"claim_path":"no-llm/no-network (structural; the fast claim check is a local HMAC verify)","det_ms":257.7,"llm_calls":30,"llm_ms":426141.3,"total_ms":426502.6,"verify_requests":34},"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","regver":"b293b9a55de591cc","runner":"pydantic_ai","schema":"plan_review_result_v2","ticket_id":"1a51-b170-5168-46d2","ticket_type":"story","verdict":"BLOCK","v